<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - FUEL SYSTEM - Fuel Transfer Pump
        - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <figure id="f1201217" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3288.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing a New O-Ring Onto the Fuel Transfer Pump</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Transfer Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Tappet</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new O-ring onto the fuel transfer pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the engine by hand until the fuel transfer pump is pushed nearly flush with the
                crankcase. Install the mounting bolts to the standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place new seal rings onto the fuel supply tube bolt and position the bolt on the fuel supply
                tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the fuel supply tube, bolts, and gaskets to the fuel transfer pump. Tighten the
                bolts to the special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the fuel supply tube nuts to the cylinder head elbows. Tighten the nuts to the
                standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the three tubes between the fuel transfer pump and the fuel filter.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
